20/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Meeting Saturday (18 January) with representatives of local authorities, President Alfred Moisiu pledged to intensify efforts to battle corruption in courts. He says his decision to restructure the Council Inspectorate will introduce efficiency and eliminate arbitrary verdicts and injustices in the judiciary.
In other news, the government announced Friday that it is boosting the price of electricity, in a bid to reduce consumption. The hike will affect private customers and businesses, but will not apply to heavy industry. (ATA, Albanian News - 18/01/03; AP - 17/01/03)
